  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws targeting money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Report suspicious transactions\n2. Verify customer identities\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Implement compliance programs\n5. Prevent money laundering activities\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution. International organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) also work to develop global standards for combating money laundering.",
